<@U0261PCRQ> / <@U02895311>  Does anyone know what text we should use in the "Your kid is too old" popup?
I defer to <@U0261PCRQ> on this one

"Daily Vroom is targeted at children ages 0 through 5. The activities included are not fitted for older children. You can still get involved. Check out <http://joinvroom.org|joinvroom.org> to learn how."
Ok, i'll put that in as the placeholder, and #warning it

I wasn't too attached to any specific blur radius. I say do what's best for performance. If we do think we need more "separation" can we simply "darken" it by overlaying some black? via alpha or otherwise?
but I'd be first down to see what it looks like
<@U026PLK4S> I can darken it a bit through code. The code already does a blend of a black overlay, so we can just decrease the transparency of that a bit and it will darken the background
cool. again, not sure we need it quite yet, but nice to know it's there.
